# 2. Complete Roadmap Overview

The cmdOS roadmap consists of five major stages.

---

# Stage 0 — Foundation

## Objective

Build the technical and organizational foundation.

## Focus Areas

- Architecture definition
- Development infrastructure
- Repository structure
- AI foundation
- Security principles

## Outcome

A complete foundation for building cmdOS.

---

# Stage 1 — MVP

## Objective

Create the first usable cmdOS product.

## Focus Areas

- User interface
- Basic AI Agent
- Basic capabilities
- Simple execution workflows

## Outcome

Users can express intent and receive executed results.

---

# Stage 2 — Agent Platform

## Objective

Transform cmdOS into an AI Agent ecosystem.

## Focus Areas

- Agent framework
- SDK ecosystem
- Plugin system
- Marketplace
- Developer tools

## Outcome

Developers can create and distribute AI Agents.

---

# Stage 3 — Execution OS

## Objective

Enable AI to operate across digital environments.

## Focus Areas

- Desktop Agent
- Mobile Agent
- Application control
- Cross-platform execution
- Workflow automation

## Outcome

AI can perform real-world computer tasks.

---

# Stage 4 — AI Native OS

## Objective

Create the future AI-native computing environment.

## Focus Areas

- Autonomous Agent networks
- Enterprise AI systems
- AI economy
- Global ecosystem

## Outcome

A complete AI Execution Operating System.

